<br>
Would be nice to see who spends the time doing it so we could send them some business. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chasefv>ChaseFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tradeskills Mod</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/6/03 8:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=614.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Idea ... </span><hr size=1> Still not 100% convinced, but leaning toward doing this eventually.<br>
<br>
That being said, what sort of information would it be convenient to include? I'm thinking about breaking it into druids/rangers, bards, Iksar, non-druid/ranger Wood Elves. Are there any other races/classes that can forage I'm not taking into account?<br>
<br>
An entry for myself would theoretically look like this:<br>
<br>
200 - Chase - No brewing forages, no plant shoots, no planar oak, no dragon eggs.<br>
(I'd refuse to part with any of the above, because I'd want to use them myself)<br>
<br>
Or would it perhaps be better to do something more along the lines of:<br>
<br>
200 - Chase - Mushrooms, Feathers (as I'm currently hanging out in Hollowshade when not actively tradeskilling, and get rather a lot of these when I'm there).<br>
<br>
Let me know what information would be useful to have for you, the potential buyer.<br>
<br>
One additional note, I will *not* document the +10% from a foraging machette (sic), for 200 foragers. The latest parses at EQTraders indicate that it has no bearing whatsoever on what you forage, it only increases the likelihood that you will have a successful forage; as 200 foragers never fail to forage *something* it is a meaningless tool for them to have.<br>
<br>
Thanx,<br>
Chase<br>
<br>
